               There is aboue an hundreth of Irish men and women that wander
about to begge for their liuing, that hath come ouer within these
two yeares. They saye they haue ben burned and spoyled by the
Earle of Desmond and report well of the Earle of Urmond.
               ¶ All these aboue written for the most part walke aboute Essex,
Middlesex, Sussex, Surrey &amp; Kent. Then let the Reader iudge what
nūbers walks in other Shieres. I feare me to great a nūber, if they
be well vnderstand.
               
